	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">mattheweston wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">So any assembler that can "assemble" 6502 code will work?</div>
<br />Yes. You just have to make sure that they output a file that respects the structure of a NES ROM. NES ROMs contain a 16-byte header, followed by the PRG-ROM banks and then the CHR-ROM banks (if the game uses CHR-RAM there are no CHR-ROM banks in the ROM).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


