	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yeah, if you haven't picked an assembler yet, don't start out with NESASM, please. The only excuse for using NESASM is if you started learning from a tutorial that used it and are already spoiled by it, but if you have the choice, don't go with it, or you'll soon find yourself wanting to switch to something else.
<br />
<br />Please pick anything but NESASM. ASM6 is probably at the same level of complexity (i.e. very low, you can get a ROM ready without hassle), but it's much less buggy and much more versatile.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
